OL,3,CTerrorist turned spy
OL,5,FScappaticci was sidelined by the IRA
OL,6,Fin 1990 when it became apparent the
OL,7,Frepublican in charge of internal
OL,8,Fsecurity was leading a double life.
OL,10,FThe team from Operation Kenova
OL,11,Fexamined dozens of abductions and
OL,12,Fmurders - not just those directly
OL,13,Flinked to Stakeknife.
OL,15,FThat's because Scappaticci wasn't the
OL,16,Fonly informant operating within the
OL,17,FIRA's 'internal security unit'.
OL,19,FOf course spying isn't a one-way
OL,20,Fstreet - it works the other way round
OL,21,Ftoo.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/5
