OL,3,CTerrorist turned spy
OL,5,FMilitary intelligence managed to
OL,6,Fsuccessfully infiltrate the IRA, and
OL,7,FUTV has spoken to someone who did just
OL,8,Fthat during the mid-1980s.
OL,10,FTo protect his identity we've called
OL,11,Fhim Alan. He was an agent within the
OL,12,FForce Research Unit which infiltrated
OL,13,Fthe IRA's northern command.
OL,15,F"The corporal said that something
OL,16,Fstrange had happened," Alan said. "He
OL,17,Fwas in a police station in Belfast and
OL,18,Fthis guy came in.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/5
